[{"text": "I come to you today to speak of liars,", "start": 12.902, "duration": 4.083}, {"text": "lawsuits", "start": 17.009, "duration": 1.423}, {"text": "and laughter.", "start": 18.456, "duration": 1.34}, {"text": "The first time I heard\nabout Holocaust denial,", "start": 20.73, "duration": 3.11}, {"text": "I laughed.", "start": 23.864, "duration": 1.302}, {"text": "Holocaust denial?", "start": 25.79, "duration": 1.752}, {"text": "The Holocaust which has\nthe dubious distinction", "start": 28.007, "duration": 3.43}, {"text": "of being the best-documented\ngenocide in the world?", "start": 31.461, "duration": 4.495}, {"text": "Who could believe it didn't happen?", "start": 36.866, "duration": 2.026}, {"text": "Think about it.", "start": 39.926, "duration": 1.347}, {"text": "For deniers to be right,", "start": 42.077, "duration": 2.281}, {"text": "who would have to be wrong?", "start": 44.382, "duration": 1.896}, {"text": "Well, first of all, the victims --", "start": 46.831, "duration": 2.766}, {"text": "the survivors who have told us\ntheir harrowing stories.", "start": 49.621, "duration": 4.717}, {"text": "Who else would have to be wrong?", "start": 55.541, "duration": 2.314}, {"text": "The bystanders.", "start": 57.879, "duration": 1.953}, {"text": "The people who lived in the myriads\nof towns and villages and cities", "start": 59.856, "duration": 3.978}, {"text": "on the Eastern front,", "start": 63.858, "duration": 1.972}, {"text": "who watched their neighbors\nbe rounded up --", "start": 65.854, "duration": 2.442}, {"text": "men, women, children, young, old --", "start": 68.32, "duration": 3.213}, {"text": "and be marched\nto the outskirts of the town", "start": 71.557, "duration": 2.72}, {"text": "to be shot and left dead in ditches.", "start": 74.301, "duration": 2.992}, {"text": "Or the Poles,", "start": 77.805, "duration": 1.33}, {"text": "who lived in towns and villages\naround the death camps,", "start": 79.159, "duration": 4.681}, {"text": "who watched day after day", "start": 83.864, "duration": 2.376}, {"text": "as the trains went in filled with people", "start": 86.264, "duration": 2.742}, {"text": "and came out empty.", "start": 89.03, "duration": 1.523}, {"text": "But above all, who would have to be wrong?", "start": 91.607, "duration": 3.633}, {"text": "The perpetrators.", "start": 95.825, "duration": 1.464}, {"text": "The people who say, \"We did it.", "start": 97.932, "duration": 2.906}, {"text": "I did it.\"", "start": 101.299, "duration": 1.524}, {"text": "Now, maybe they add a caveat.", "start": 102.847, "duration": 2.149}, {"text": "They say, \"I didn't have a choice;\nI was forced to do it.\"", "start": 105.02, "duration": 4.424}, {"text": "But nonetheless, they say, \"I did it.\"", "start": 109.924, "duration": 2.669}, {"text": "Think about it.", "start": 113.758, "duration": 1.551}, {"text": "In not one war crimes trial\nsince the end of World War II", "start": 115.333, "duration": 5.939}, {"text": "has a perpetrator of any nationality\never said, \"It didn't happen.\"", "start": 121.296, "duration": 6.636}, {"text": "Again, they may have said, \"I was forced,\"\nbut never that it didn't happen.", "start": 128.898, "duration": 4.582}, {"text": "Having thought that through,", "start": 133.504, "duration": 1.474}, {"text": "I decided denial was not\ngoing to be on my agenda;", "start": 135.002, "duration": 3.951}, {"text": "I had bigger things to worry about,\nto write about, to research,", "start": 138.977, "duration": 3.708}, {"text": "and I moved on.", "start": 142.709, "duration": 1.314}, {"text": "Fast-forward a little over a decade,", "start": 144.731, "duration": 2.819}, {"text": "and two senior scholars --", "start": 147.574, "duration": 1.812}, {"text": "two of the most prominent historians\nof the Holocaust --", "start": 149.41, "duration": 3.158}, {"text": "approached me and said,", "start": 152.592, "duration": 1.257}, {"text": "\"Deborah, let's have coffee.", "start": 153.873, "duration": 1.789}, {"text": "We have a research idea\nthat we think is perfect for you.\"", "start": 155.686, "duration": 3.597}, {"text": "Intrigued and flattered\nthat they came to me with an idea", "start": 159.307, "duration": 3.833}, {"text": "and thought me worthy of it,", "start": 163.164, "duration": 1.577}, {"text": "I asked, \"What is it?\"", "start": 164.765, "duration": 2.096}, {"text": "And they said, \"Holocaust denial.\"", "start": 167.485, "duration": 2.989}, {"text": "And for the second time, I laughed.", "start": 171.173, "duration": 2.495}, {"text": "Holocaust denial?", "start": 174.156, "duration": 1.924}, {"text": "The Flat Earth folks?", "start": 176.104, "duration": 1.986}, {"text": "The Elvis-is-alive people?", "start": 178.114, "duration": 2.137}, {"text": "I should study them?", "start": 180.275, "duration": 2.188}, {"text": "And these two guys said,", "start": 183.146, "duration": 1.317}, {"text": "\"Yeah, we're intrigued.", "start": 184.487, "duration": 1.933}, {"text": "What are they about?", "start": 186.832, "duration": 1.572}, {"text": "What's their objective?", "start": 188.428, "duration": 1.75}, {"text": "How do they manage to get people\nto believe what they say?\"", "start": 190.202, "duration": 3.654}, {"text": "So thinking, if they thought\nit was worthwhile,", "start": 194.576, "duration": 3.528}, {"text": "I would take a momentary diversion --", "start": 198.128, "duration": 3.374}, {"text": "maybe a year, maybe two,\nthree, maybe even four --", "start": 201.526, "duration": 2.938}, {"text": "in academic terms, that's momentary.", "start": 204.488, "duration": 2.245}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 206.757, "duration": 1.142}, {"text": "We work very slowly.", "start": 207.923, "duration": 2.387}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 210.334, "duration": 1.572}, {"text": "And I would look at them.", "start": 211.93, "duration": 1.802}, {"text": "So I did.", "start": 213.756, "duration": 1.155}, {"text": "I did my research, and I came up\nwith a number of things,", "start": 214.935, "duration": 2.839}, {"text": "two of which I'd like to share\nwith you today.", "start": 217.798, "duration": 2.593}, {"text": "One:", "start": 220.415, "duration": 1.333}, {"text": "deniers are wolves in sheep's clothing.", "start": 221.772, "duration": 4.957}, {"text": "They are the same: Nazis, neo-Nazis --", "start": 227.532, "duration": 2.965}, {"text": "you can decide whether you want\nto put a \"neo\" there or not.", "start": 230.521, "duration": 3.227}, {"text": "But when I looked at them,", "start": 234.606, "duration": 2.333}, {"text": "I didn't see any SS-like uniforms,", "start": 236.963, "duration": 4.726}, {"text": "swastika-like symbols on the wall,", "start": 241.713, "duration": 3.151}, {"text": "Sieg Heil salutes --", "start": 244.888, "duration": 2.057}, {"text": "none of that.", "start": 246.969, "duration": 1.544}, {"text": "What I found instead", "start": 248.537, "duration": 2.87}, {"text": "were people parading\nas respectable academics.", "start": 251.431, "duration": 4.615}, {"text": "What did they have?", "start": 256.736, "duration": 1.221}, {"text": "They had an institute.", "start": 257.981, "duration": 1.698}, {"text": "An \"Institute for Historical Review.\"", "start": 259.703, "duration": 3.844}, {"text": "They had a journal -- a slick journal --", "start": 264.212, "duration": 2.554}, {"text": "a \"Journal of Historical Review.\"", "start": 266.79, "duration": 2.954}, {"text": "One filled with papers --", "start": 270.218, "duration": 2.706}, {"text": "footnote-laden papers.", "start": 272.948, "duration": 2.044}, {"text": "And they had a new name.", "start": 275.743, "duration": 1.94}, {"text": "Not neo-Nazis,", "start": 278.32, "duration": 2.168}, {"text": "not anti-Semites --", "start": 280.512, "duration": 2.49}, {"text": "revisionists.", "start": 283.026, "duration": 1.258}, {"text": "They said, \"We are revisionists.", "start": 284.811, "duration": 2.215}, {"text": "We are out to do one thing:", "start": 287.05, "duration": 2.683}, {"text": "to revise mistakes in history.\"", "start": 289.757, "duration": 3.56}, {"text": "But all you had to do was go\none inch below the surface,", "start": 294.189, "duration": 5.41}, {"text": "and what did you find there?", "start": 299.623, "duration": 1.907}, {"text": "The same adulation of Hitler,", "start": 301.554, "duration": 2.49}, {"text": "praise of the Third Reich,", "start": 304.068, "duration": 1.875}, {"text": "anti-Semitism, racism, prejudice.", "start": 305.967, "duration": 2.942}, {"text": "This is what intrigued me.", "start": 309.724, "duration": 2.446}, {"text": "It was anti-Semitism, racism, prejudice,\nparading as rational discourse.", "start": 312.194, "duration": 6.997}, {"text": "The other thing I found --", "start": 320.55, "duration": 1.587}, {"text": "many of us have been taught to think\nthere are facts and there are opinions --", "start": 322.161, "duration": 3.745}, {"text": "after studying deniers,", "start": 325.93, "duration": 1.456}, {"text": "I think differently.", "start": 327.41, "duration": 1.336}, {"text": "There are facts,", "start": 329.258, "duration": 1.648}, {"text": "there are opinions,", "start": 330.93, "duration": 1.714}, {"text": "and there are lies.", "start": 332.668, "duration": 1.612}, {"text": "And what deniers want to do\nis take their lies,", "start": 334.969, "duration": 4.426}, {"text": "dress them up as opinions --", "start": 340.385, "duration": 1.632}, {"text": "maybe edgy opinions,", "start": 342.041, "duration": 1.99}, {"text": "maybe sort of out-of-the-box opinions --", "start": 344.055, "duration": 2.709}, {"text": "but then if they're opinions,", "start": 346.788, "duration": 1.384}, {"text": "they should be part of the conversation.", "start": 348.196, "duration": 2.132}, {"text": "And then they encroach on the facts.", "start": 350.352, "duration": 3.393}, {"text": "I published my work --", "start": 355.125, "duration": 1.563}, {"text": "the book was published,", "start": 356.712, "duration": 1.174}, {"text": "\"Denying the Holocaust: The Growing\nAssault on Truth and Memory,\"", "start": 357.91, "duration": 3.402}, {"text": "it came out in many different countries,", "start": 361.336, "duration": 1.956}, {"text": "including here in Penguin UK,", "start": 363.316, "duration": 2.16}, {"text": "and I was done with those folks\nand ready to move on.", "start": 365.5, "duration": 3.43}, {"text": "Then came the letter from Penguin UK.", "start": 369.983, "duration": 3.708}, {"text": "And for the third time, I laughed ...", "start": 374.254, "duration": 2.768}, {"text": "mistakenly.", "start": 378.908, "duration": 1.24}, {"text": "I opened the letter,", "start": 380.792, "duration": 1.73}, {"text": "and it informed me that David Irving\nwas bringing a libel suit against me", "start": 382.546, "duration": 5.888}, {"text": "in the United Kingdom", "start": 388.458, "duration": 1.597}, {"text": "for calling him a Holocaust denier.", "start": 390.079, "duration": 3.036}, {"text": "David Irving suing me?", "start": 393.773, "duration": 1.934}, {"text": "Who was David Irving?", "start": 395.731, "duration": 1.204}, {"text": "David Irving was a writer\nof historical works,", "start": 396.959, "duration": 2.607}, {"text": "most of them about World War II,", "start": 399.59, "duration": 2.023}, {"text": "and virtually all of those works\ntook the position", "start": 401.637, "duration": 3.219}, {"text": "that the Nazis were really not so bad,", "start": 404.88, "duration": 3.578}, {"text": "and the Allies were really not so good.", "start": 408.482, "duration": 3.084}, {"text": "And the Jews, whatever happened to them,", "start": 411.59, "duration": 2.105}, {"text": "they sort of deserved it.", "start": 413.719, "duration": 1.31}, {"text": "He knew the documents,", "start": 416.026, "duration": 1.491}, {"text": "he knew the facts,", "start": 417.541, "duration": 1.443}, {"text": "but he somehow twisted them\nto get this opinion.", "start": 419.008, "duration": 3.172}, {"text": "He hadn't always been a Holocaust denier,", "start": 422.836, "duration": 2.512}, {"text": "but in the late '80s,", "start": 425.372, "duration": 1.741}, {"text": "he embraced it with great vigor.", "start": 427.137, "duration": 2.427}, {"text": "The reason I laughed also\nwas this was a man", "start": 431.337, "duration": 3.905}, {"text": "who not only was a Holocaust denier,", "start": 435.266, "duration": 1.934}, {"text": "but seemed quite proud of it.", "start": 437.224, "duration": 1.695}, {"text": "Here was a man -- and I quote --", "start": 438.943, "duration": 1.624}, {"text": "who said, \"I'm going to sink\nthe battleship Auschwitz.\"", "start": 440.591, "duration": 3.694}, {"text": "Here was a man", "start": 445.165, "duration": 1.172}, {"text": "who pointed to the number tattooed\non a survivor's arm and said,", "start": 446.361, "duration": 4.02}, {"text": "\"How much money have you made", "start": 451.536, "duration": 1.592}, {"text": "from having that number\ntattooed on your arm?\"", "start": 453.152, "duration": 3.4}, {"text": "Here was a man who said,", "start": 457.369, "duration": 1.908}, {"text": "\"More people died in Senator Kennedy's car", "start": 459.301, "duration": 2.956}, {"text": "at Chappaquiddick", "start": 462.281, "duration": 1.312}, {"text": "than died in gas chambers at Auschwitz.\"", "start": 463.617, "duration": 3.314}, {"text": "That's an American reference,\nbut you can look it up.", "start": 466.955, "duration": 2.837}, {"text": "This was not a man who seemed\nat all ashamed or reticent", "start": 471.226, "duration": 3.014}, {"text": "about being a Holocaust denier.", "start": 474.264, "duration": 2.069}, {"text": "Now, lots of my academic\ncolleagues counseled me --", "start": 476.956, "duration": 3.78}, {"text": "\"Eh, Deborah, just ignore it.\"", "start": 480.76, "duration": 1.906}, {"text": "When I explained you can't just\nignore a libel suit,", "start": 482.69, "duration": 3.588}, {"text": "they said, \"Who's going to\nbelieve him anyway?\"", "start": 486.302, "duration": 2.782}, {"text": "But here was the problem:", "start": 489.603, "duration": 2.08}, {"text": "British law put the onus,\nput the burden of proof on me", "start": 491.707, "duration": 5.308}, {"text": "to prove the truth of what I said,", "start": 497.039, "duration": 2.682}, {"text": "in contrast to as it would have\nbeen in the United States", "start": 499.745, "duration": 2.763}, {"text": "and in many other countries:", "start": 502.532, "duration": 1.504}, {"text": "on him to prove the falsehood.", "start": 504.06, "duration": 3.006}, {"text": "What did that mean?", "start": 507.741, "duration": 1.461}, {"text": "That meant if I didn't fight,", "start": 509.226, "duration": 3.376}, {"text": "he would win by default.", "start": 512.626, "duration": 2.426}, {"text": "And if he won by default,", "start": 515.611, "duration": 1.755}, {"text": "he could then legitimately say,", "start": 517.39, "duration": 2.641}, {"text": "\"My David Irving version of the Holocaust\nis a legitimate version.", "start": 520.055, "duration": 5.336}, {"text": "Deborah Lipstadt was found\nto have libeled me", "start": 525.415, "duration": 2.184}, {"text": "when she called me a Holocaust denier.", "start": 527.623, "duration": 1.947}, {"text": "Ipso facto, I, David Irving,\nam not a Holocaust denier.\"", "start": 529.594, "duration": 4.428}, {"text": "And what is that version?", "start": 534.046, "duration": 1.712}, {"text": "There was no plan to murder the Jews,", "start": 536.251, "duration": 2.996}, {"text": "there were no gas chambers,", "start": 539.271, "duration": 2.052}, {"text": "there were no mass shootings,", "start": 541.347, "duration": 1.856}, {"text": "Hitler had nothing to do\nwith any suffering that went on,", "start": 543.227, "duration": 3.171}, {"text": "and the Jews have made this all up", "start": 546.422, "duration": 3.805}, {"text": "to get money from Germany", "start": 550.251, "duration": 2.398}, {"text": "and to get a state,", "start": 552.673, "duration": 1.707}, {"text": "and they've done it with the aid\nand abettance of the Allies --", "start": 554.404, "duration": 3.377}, {"text": "they've planted the documents\nand planted the evidence.", "start": 557.805, "duration": 3.465}, {"text": "I couldn't let that stand", "start": 562.28, "duration": 2.38}, {"text": "and ever face a survivor", "start": 564.684, "duration": 2.2}, {"text": "or a child of survivors.", "start": 567.643, "duration": 1.975}, {"text": "I couldn't let that stand", "start": 569.642, "duration": 2.152}, {"text": "and consider myself\na responsible historian.", "start": 571.818, "duration": 4.251}, {"text": "So we fought.", "start": 577.007, "duration": 1.745}, {"text": "And for those of you\nwho haven't seen \"Denial,\"", "start": 578.776, "duration": 2.282}, {"text": "spoiler alert:", "start": 581.082, "duration": 1.159}, {"text": "we won.", "start": 582.265, "duration": 1.218}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 583.507, "duration": 1.295}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 584.826, "duration": 2.567}, {"text": "The judge found David Irving", "start": 591.808, "duration": 4.241}, {"text": "to be a liar,", "start": 596.073, "duration": 3.331}, {"text": "a racist,", "start": 599.428, "duration": 1.163}, {"text": "an anti-Semite.", "start": 600.615, "duration": 1.254}, {"text": "His view of history was tendentious,", "start": 601.893, "duration": 2.36}, {"text": "he lied, he distorted --", "start": 604.277, "duration": 1.926}, {"text": "and most importantly,", "start": 606.227, "duration": 2.643}, {"text": "he did it deliberately.", "start": 608.894, "duration": 2.113}, {"text": "We showed a pattern,\nin over 25 different major instances.", "start": 611.031, "duration": 4.139}, {"text": "Not small things -- many of us\nin this audience write books,", "start": 615.194, "duration": 3.11}, {"text": "are writing books;", "start": 618.328, "duration": 1.185}, {"text": "we always make mistakes, that's why\nwe're glad to have second editions:", "start": 619.537, "duration": 3.466}, {"text": "correct the mistakes.", "start": 623.027, "duration": 1.186}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 624.237, "duration": 1.15}, {"text": "But these always moved\nin the same direction:", "start": 626.454, "duration": 3.136}, {"text": "blame the Jews,", "start": 630.438, "duration": 2.211}, {"text": "exonerate the Nazis.", "start": 632.673, "duration": 2.175}, {"text": "But how did we win?", "start": 635.52, "duration": 1.584}, {"text": "What we did is follow his footnotes\nback to his sources.", "start": 638.016, "duration": 5.38}, {"text": "And what did we find?", "start": 644.01, "duration": 1.783}, {"text": "Not in most cases,", "start": 645.817, "duration": 1.479}, {"text": "and not in the preponderance of cases,", "start": 647.32, "duration": 1.968}, {"text": "but in every single instance where\nhe made some reference to the Holocaust,", "start": 649.312, "duration": 4.311}, {"text": "that his supposed evidence was distorted,", "start": 653.647, "duration": 4.242}, {"text": "half-truth,", "start": 657.913, "duration": 1.42}, {"text": "date-changed,", "start": 659.357, "duration": 1.334}, {"text": "sequence-changed,", "start": 660.715, "duration": 2.187}, {"text": "someone put at a meeting who wasn't there.", "start": 662.926, "duration": 2.124}, {"text": "In other words,\nhe didn't have the evidence.", "start": 665.074, "duration": 2.761}, {"text": "His evidence didn't prove it.", "start": 667.859, "duration": 2.109}, {"text": "We didn't prove what happened.", "start": 669.992, "duration": 2.659}, {"text": "We proved that what he said happened --", "start": 673.448, "duration": 2.499}, {"text": "and by extension, all deniers,\nbecause he either quotes them", "start": 675.971, "duration": 2.86}, {"text": "or they get their arguments from him --", "start": 678.855, "duration": 2.471}, {"text": "is not true.", "start": 681.35, "duration": 1.246}, {"text": "What they claim --", "start": 682.62, "duration": 1.189}, {"text": "they don't have the evidence to prove it.", "start": 683.833, "duration": 2.622}, {"text": "So why is my story\nmore than just the story", "start": 688.429, "duration": 4.744}, {"text": "of a quirky, long,\nsix-year, difficult lawsuit,", "start": 693.197, "duration": 3.807}, {"text": "an American professor\nbeing dragged into a courtroom", "start": 697.028, "duration": 4.989}, {"text": "by a man that the court\ndeclared in its judgment", "start": 702.041, "duration": 3.044}, {"text": "was a neo-Nazi polemicist?", "start": 705.109, "duration": 2.25}, {"text": "What message does it have?", "start": 707.383, "duration": 1.783}, {"text": "I think in the context\nof the question of truth,", "start": 709.62, "duration": 2.973}, {"text": "it has a very significant message.", "start": 712.617, "duration": 2.462}, {"text": "Because today,", "start": 715.103, "duration": 1.785}, {"text": "as we well know,", "start": 716.912, "duration": 1.666}, {"text": "truth and facts are under assault.", "start": 718.602, "duration": 4.116}, {"text": "Social media, for all\nthe gifts it has given us,", "start": 723.522, "duration": 3.252}, {"text": "has also allowed the difference\nbetween facts -- established facts --", "start": 726.798, "duration": 5.581}, {"text": "and lies", "start": 732.403, "duration": 1.757}, {"text": "to be flattened.", "start": 734.184, "duration": 1.398}, {"text": "Third of all:", "start": 736.81, "duration": 1.51}, {"text": "extremism.", "start": 738.344, "duration": 1.471}, {"text": "You may not see Ku Klux Klan robes,", "start": 740.807, "duration": 3.577}, {"text": "you may not see burning crosses,", "start": 744.408, "duration": 2.071}, {"text": "you may not even hear outright\nwhite supremacist language.", "start": 746.503, "duration": 4.319}, {"text": "It may go by names: \"alt-right,\"\n\"National Front\" -- pick your names.", "start": 750.846, "duration": 4.906}, {"text": "But underneath, it's that same extremism\nthat I found in Holocaust denial", "start": 755.776, "duration": 5.835}, {"text": "parading as rational discourse.", "start": 761.635, "duration": 3.394}, {"text": "We live in an age\nwhere truth is on the defensive.", "start": 766.954, "duration": 5.217}, {"text": "I'm reminded of a New Yorker cartoon.", "start": 772.195, "duration": 2.484}, {"text": "A quiz show recently appeared\nin \"The New Yorker\"", "start": 774.703, "duration": 2.52}, {"text": "where the host of the quiz show\nis saying to one of the contestants,", "start": 777.247, "duration": 3.222}, {"text": "\"Yes, ma'am, you had the right answer.", "start": 780.493, "duration": 2.309}, {"text": "But your opponent yelled\nmore loudly than you did,", "start": 782.826, "duration": 2.493}, {"text": "so he gets the point.\"", "start": 785.343, "duration": 1.525}, {"text": "What can we do?", "start": 788.048, "duration": 1.507}, {"text": "First of all,", "start": 790.377, "duration": 1.377}, {"text": "we cannot be beguiled\nby rational appearances.", "start": 791.778, "duration": 5.431}, {"text": "We've got to look underneath,", "start": 797.233, "duration": 1.769}, {"text": "and we will find there the extremism.", "start": 799.026, "duration": 2.801}, {"text": "Second of all,", "start": 802.811, "duration": 1.986}, {"text": "we must understand\nthat truth is not relative.", "start": 804.821, "duration": 6.081}, {"text": "Number three,", "start": 812.957, "duration": 1.464}, {"text": "we must go on the offensive,", "start": 814.445, "duration": 3.689}, {"text": "not the defensive.", "start": 818.158, "duration": 1.773}, {"text": "When someone makes an outrageous claim,", "start": 820.496, "duration": 2.607}, {"text": "even though they may hold\none of the highest offices in the land,", "start": 823.127, "duration": 3.504}, {"text": "if not the world --", "start": 826.655, "duration": 2.011}, {"text": "we must say to them,", "start": 828.69, "duration": 1.51}, {"text": "\"Where's the proof?", "start": 830.224, "duration": 1.966}, {"text": "Where's the evidence?\"", "start": 832.214, "duration": 2.137}, {"text": "We must hold their feet to the fire.", "start": 834.375, "duration": 2.927}, {"text": "We must not treat it as if their lies\nare the same as the facts.", "start": 837.326, "duration": 4.606}, {"text": "And as I said earlier,\ntruth is not relative.", "start": 843.215, "duration": 3.54}, {"text": "Many of us have grown up\nin the world of the academy", "start": 846.779, "duration": 2.856}, {"text": "and enlightened liberal thought,", "start": 849.659, "duration": 1.741}, {"text": "where we're taught\neverything is open to debate.", "start": 851.424, "duration": 2.961}, {"text": "But that's not the case.", "start": 854.984, "duration": 2.014}, {"text": "There are certain things that are true.", "start": 857.022, "duration": 3.442}, {"text": "There are indisputable facts --", "start": 861.012, "duration": 3.02}, {"text": "objective truths.", "start": 864.056, "duration": 1.69}, {"text": "Galileo taught it to us centuries ago.", "start": 866.339, "duration": 4.817}, {"text": "Even after being forced\nto recant by the Vatican", "start": 871.18, "duration": 4.667}, {"text": "that the Earth moved around the Sun,", "start": 875.871, "duration": 2.573}, {"text": "he came out,", "start": 878.468, "duration": 1.154}, {"text": "and what is he reported to have said?", "start": 879.646, "duration": 2.31}, {"text": "\"And yet, it still moves.\"", "start": 881.98, "duration": 3.822}, {"text": "The Earth is not flat.", "start": 887.162, "duration": 2.84}, {"text": "The climate is changing.", "start": 890.026, "duration": 2.29}, {"text": "Elvis is not alive.", "start": 893.207, "duration": 2.268}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 895.499, "duration": 1.535}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 897.058, "duration": 2.316}, {"text": "And most importantly,", "start": 899.398, "duration": 2.301}, {"text": "truth and fact are under assault.", "start": 901.723, "duration": 4.649}, {"text": "The job ahead of us,", "start": 907.109, "duration": 1.61}, {"text": "the task ahead of us,", "start": 908.743, "duration": 1.203}, {"text": "the challenge ahead of us", "start": 909.97, "duration": 1.594}, {"text": "is great.", "start": 911.588, "duration": 1.234}, {"text": "The time to fight is short.", "start": 913.567, "duration": 2.637}, {"text": "We must act now.", "start": 917.061, "duration": 2.843}, {"text": "Later will be too late.", "start": 920.749, "duration": 3.245}, {"text": "Thank you very much.", "start": 924.018, "duration": 1.262}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 925.304, "duration": 4.046}]